DATA CLOUD
Cumulus Establishes Data Foundation Requirements

Cumulus Bank and Financial Services want to integrate Data Cloud with Marketing Cloud Engagement. They’re using Data Cloud to establish a data foundation in Marketing Cloud Engagement. They then want to use the data foundation as part of their campaigns, including their initial customer campaign: a 30-day journey to welcome new auto policy holders and to introduce them to their policy and benefits.

Identify Common Content Personalization Attributes for Event-Triggered Journeys

They decide to create event-triggered campaigns for:

Policy Onboarding—A 30-day journey to welcome new auto policyholders and to introduce them to their benefits.
Credit Signup—A 14-day journey to deliver progress updates and solicit feedback after a consumer signs up for a new line of credit.
Journey Decisioning for Audience-Based Campaigns
CAMPAIGN	ATTRIBUTE	DATA CLOUD DATA TYPE	JOURNEY DATA TYPE
Upcoming Payment Reminder	Customer Credit Balance	Individual	Contact Data
Policy Upsell	Policy Type	Unified Individual	Contact Data
Journey Decisioning for Event-Triggered Campaigns

Policy Onboarding	eBilling Enrollment Status	Individual	Contact Data
Credit Signup	Credit Application Status	Individual	Contact Data
Credit Signup	Applicant Feedback Status	Individual	Contact Data

Determine Which Contact Model Works Best

Cumulus Bank and Financial Services are an international company with a full audience of nearly 10 million contacts shared across 10 countries and five operating units. Although the company is new to Marketing Cloud Engagement, they have a large team that plans to build moderately sophisticated journeys over the next year. They estimate that they’ll need approximately 150 attributes in the data foundation within Engagement to satisfy all potential campaigns over the next year.

Together, the team at Cumulus Bank and Financial Services decides to implement the Collective Core Audience Model pattern in Engagement. Because they’re choosing to implement the Collective Core Audience Model, the team categorizes their chosen required attributes (Contact Data) in preparation for their multiple Data Cloud activations.
